<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-24T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="890" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">662.11173 Barley/38: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-24T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">October 24,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 24—10:05
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>217.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Reference my 215, October 23, 10 a.m. According to very confidential
                            information, yesterday at stormy meeting private interests <pb facs="1033" n="915" xml:id="pg_915"/> and competent ministries
                            decided for present to defer embargo. Its proponents were embarrassed
                            because of failure of scientific investigation so far to produce
                            definite explanation regarding barley’s alleged nocuous character.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>